@database INDEX_CD
@node main "INDEX"

 Index for Aminet CD-ROM  -  Public Domain
 ============================================
 $VER: 1.00 (28-04-1997) ©by Claudio Buraglio

 This tool is like FINDKIT (on Aminet CD-ROM's) plus a browser in
 Amigaguide format for your Aminet CD.

 The programm is made to have a complete support of this players:

   Delitracker
   Hippoplayer
   MultiPlayer
   OctaMed Soundstudio (!!)

 Of course in your system the ARexx interface must be on work.

 @{"History                " LINK NUO}
 @{"System requirements    " LINK REQ}
 @{"Usage                  " LINK IND}
 @{"Author                 " LINK AUT}


Sorry for this poor document. Is incomplete.

@ENDNODE

@NODE REQ "System requirements"

System requirements
-------------------

Amiga OS 2.0+ or OS 3.0+ to use the Prefs with MUI.


Command needed:

Path+Comando      Comment
===============   ============================================================

sys:Rexxc/RX      To execute the control command for the players:
                  HippoPlayer, DeliTracker, MultiPlayer, SoundStudio.
c:Assign          Assign the progdir ICD:
c:Copy            Used by IndexCreator.
c:Delete          Remove the old file from destdir.
c:ED              Editor used by 'Prefs' when MUI is not present.
c:Execute         To execute the batch.
c:Info            Used by IndexCreator to find the device with Aminet.
c:Rename          Used when a module is played.
c:RequestChoice   This is the requester for the choices.
c:RequestFile     To select other destination directory.
c:Run             To execute Delitracker e the program from AmigaGuide.

...and 'sys:Utilities/AmigaGuide' .

@ENDNODE


@NODE IND "Usage"

How to make an Index.
---------------------

 Insert an Aminet CD-ROM on your drive an click on the 'IndexCreator' icon
 to made the index of this CD.

 Repeat this operation for every Aminet CD-ROM that you own.


How to use the utility.
-----------------------

 Now click on 'Find'    icon to search a file with a specific pattern
  or click on 'IndexCD' to browse your CD's.


How to configure the utility.
-----------------------------

 Click on Prefs icon.

 If You have the @{"MUI" LINK MUI} a window to specify the path of yours tools is showed,
 otherwise the ED editor is used to specify the path.

@ENDNODE



@ENDNODE

@NODE NUO "History."


  Version 1  - 26-Feb-97
  =======================

  First version that work on Aminet CD-ROM.

  This is a modification of the program that I have made for the italian
  magazine+CD 'EnigmA Amiga Run' (EAR).
  The support of the EAR CD-ROM's are removed (the directory tree, CD labels,
  month after month, is not stable).

@ENDNODE

